IssueDetail.Description:
The diagnostics and dotnet-diagnostictests repo's need to install arm/arm64 runtimes and this prevents it:

Line 166 dotnet-install.ps1:
```
function Get-CLIArchitecture-From-Architecture([string]$Architecture) {
    Say-Invocation $MyInvocation

    switch ($Architecture.ToLower()) {
        { $_ -eq "<auto>" } { return Get-CLIArchitecture-From-Architecture $(Get-Machine-Architecture) }
        { ($_ -eq "amd64") -or ($_ -eq "x64") } { return "x64" }
        { $_ -eq "x86" } { return "x86" }
        default { throw "Architecture not supported. If you think this is a bug please report it at https://github.com/dotnet/cli/issues" }
    }
}    
```
These two lines need to be added to the switch:
```
    { $_ -eq "arm" } { return "arm" }
    { $_ -eq "arm64" } { return "arm64" }
```

IssueDetail.Title_Description:
dotnet-install.ps1 doesn't allow arm/arm64 runtimes to be installed The diagnostics and dotnet-diagnostictests repo's need to install arm/arm64 runtimes and this prevents it:

Line 166 dotnet-install.ps1:
```
function Get-CLIArchitecture-From-Architecture([string]$Architecture) {
    Say-Invocation $MyInvocation

    switch ($Architecture.ToLower()) {
        { $_ -eq "<auto>" } { return Get-CLIArchitecture-From-Architecture $(Get-Machine-Architecture) }
        { ($_ -eq "amd64") -or ($_ -eq "x64") } { return "x64" }
        { $_ -eq "x86" } { return "x86" }
        default { throw "Architecture not supported. If you think this is a bug please report it at https://github.com/dotnet/cli/issues" }
    }
}    
```
These two lines need to be added to the switch:
```
    { $_ -eq "arm" } { return "arm" }
    { $_ -eq "arm64" } { return "arm64" }
```

